# Testing Rules

## Required Before Commit

- Run `corepack yarn test:update` after behavior/UI changes that affect snapshots
- Run `corepack yarn test:typecheck` for TypeScript safety
- Run `corepack yarn test:code` for lint validation when touching TS/TSX files

## Scope-Aware Test Runs

- For component/editor logic in `packages/*`: run `corepack yarn test:update` and relevant package tests first
- For app behavior in `excalidraw-app/*`: run app tests via `corepack yarn test:app --watch=false`
- Before merge or release-sensitive changes: run `corepack yarn test:all`

## Test Quality

- Keep tests colocated with implementation when practical
- Update snapshots only for intentional UI/behavior changes
- Do not weaken assertions just to pass tests
- Do not skip failing tests without explicit approval

## How to verify

- Run `corepack yarn test:typecheck`.
- Run `corepack yarn test:code` for changed TS/TSX paths.
- If snapshots are affected, run `corepack yarn test:update`.
- For app-level behavior changes, run `corepack yarn test:app --watch=false`.
- Before merge on broad/risky changes, run `corepack yarn test:all`.
- Confirm no `@ts-ignore`, unnecessary `any`, or assertion weakening was added to force passing tests.



